info: The “Open Data Challenge Prize: Lessons learned innovation workshop” was organized by Open Data Institute and facilitated by Kateryna Onyiliogwu and Amanda Smith.

session.description: Open data accelerators and incubators met to showcase experiences and lessons of the programmes and their interactions with the community.

conference_notes: CKAN developers are a lively community with an increasing amount of development of new extensions. Extensions are becoming a powerful tool to adapt CKAN to multiple needs. Thus quite different use cases were presented, from those focused on the classic open data storage to others involving private sector or to extend its range of applications to linked data.
